    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect power control adjustment in UL scheduler\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_ue_max_mcs_min_rb` function in the UL scheduler was not properly respecting the target TBS when adjusting MCS and RB allocation for power control. This led to situations where the scheduled transmission would not meet the required data size.\n\nThe function was ignoring the input `tbs` parameter and recalculating TBS based on current MCS/RB allocation, which meant it wasn't respecting the target data transmission requirements.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler_ulsch.c`: Modified `nr_ue_max_mcs_min_rb` to properly use the input TBS parameter as target for power calculations\n- Simplified RB reduction logic to properly track power consumption\n- Maintained original approach of reducing RBs first, then MCS for power constraint compliance\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain channel conditions with tight power constraints, UEs would experience repeated scheduling failures as the computed TBS after power adjustment was insufficient to carry the buffered data. This manifested as:\n- Stuck RLC queues at the gNB\n- Retransmission timeouts at the UE\n- Poor uplink throughput for edge UEs\n\nThe issue was most observable with UEs reporting low PHR values in poor coverage areas.\n"
}